info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 06 at 2:45AM MST until February 06 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM MST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 mph with gusts up to 70 mph possible. * WHERE...Southern Laramie Range, adjacent Foothills, and central Laramie County including the city of Cheyenne. * WHEN...Until 11 AM MST this morning. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
